subSubSection.paragraph:
Female genitalia
: Subgenital plate and gonapophyses typical for the genus, only external valvula well developed, bearing 6 apically hooked setae near broadly rounded apex. Spermapore sclerite a thick and heavily sclerotized plate, proximally broadly rounded, distally narrowly rounded (
Fig. 2F
); spermathecal duct curved inside the sclerite (
Fig. 2G
) and widened towards spermathecal vesicle shortly after the spermapore sclerite (length of the narrow portion of the duct, before widening, about 1.5 times length of spermapore sclerite).
